init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is now the only nation on the planet.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US government decides to send a team of astronauts to the Moon to see if there is any life there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The astronauts are sent to the Moon to find out if this is true.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The astronauts land on the Moon and find a small colony of people who have been living there for 50 years.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are a very peaceful people, and don't want to be bothered by anyone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The astronauts are sent back to Earth with the message that the Moon citizens want to be left alone.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The US government decides that the Moon citizens must be destroyed, and sends a team of astronauts to the Moon to destroy the colony.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The astronauts land on the Moon and find that the Moon citizens are not willing to fight for their lives.
